description: This operation returns detailed information about a specified domain that is associated with the current Amazon Web Services account. Contact information for the domain is also returned as part of the output.

parameters.name: DomainName
parameters.description: The name of the domain that you want to get detailed information about.

nested_items.name: DomainName
nested_items.description: The name of a domain.

nested_items.name: Nameservers
nested_items.description: The name servers of the domain.

nested_items.name: Name
nested_items.description: The fully qualified host name of the name server.

nested_items.name: GlueIps
nested_items.description: Glue IP address of a name server entry. Glue IP addresses are required only when the name of the name server is a subdomain of the domain. For example, if your domain is example.com and the name server for the domain is ns.example.com, you need to specify the IP address for ns.example.com.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: AutoRenew
nested_items.description: Specifies whether the domain registration is set to renew automatically.

nested_items.name: AdminContact
nested_items.description: Provides details about the domain administrative contact.

nested_items.name: FirstName
nested_items.description: First name of contact.

nested_items.name: LastName
nested_items.description: Last name of contact.

nested_items.name: ContactType
nested_items.description: Indicates whether the contact is a person, company, association, or public organization. Note the following:
If you specify a value other than PERSON, you must also specify a value for OrganizationName.

For some TLDs, the privacy protection available depends on the value that you specify for Contact Type. For the privacy protection settings for your TLD, see Domains that You Can Register with Amazon Route 53 in the Amazon Route 53 Developer Guide.
For .es domains, the value of ContactType must be PERSON for all three contacts.

nested_items.name: OrganizationName
nested_items.description: Name of the organization for contact types other than PERSON.

nested_items.name: AddressLine1
nested_items.description: First line of the contact's address.

nested_items.name: AddressLine2
nested_items.description: Second line of contact's address, if any.

nested_items.name: City
nested_items.description: The city of the contact's address.

nested_items.name: State
nested_items.description: The state or province of the contact's city.

nested_items.name: CountryCode
nested_items.description: Code for the country of the contact's address.

nested_items.name: ZipCode
nested_items.description: The zip or postal code of the contact's address.

nested_items.name: PhoneNumber
nested_items.description: The phone number of the contact.

nested_items.name: Email
nested_items.description: Email address of the contact.

nested_items.name: Fax
nested_items.description: Fax number of the contact.

nested_items.name: ExtraParams
nested_items.description: A list of name-value pairs for parameters required by certain top-level domains.

nested_items.name: Name

AU_ID_NUMBER.
AU_ID_TYPE Valid values include the following:
BRAND_NUMBER.
CA_BUSINESS_ENTITY_TYPE Valid values include the following:
CA_LEGAL_TYPE When ContactType is PERSON, valid values include the following:

nested_items.type: Legal Representative of a Canadian Citizen or Permanent Resident

nested_items.name: AdminPrivacy
nested_items.description: Specifies whether contact information is concealed from WHOIS queries. If the value is true, WHOIS ('who is') queries return contact information either for Amazon Registrar or for our registrar associate, Gandi. If the value is false, WHOIS queries return the information that you entered for the admin contact.

nested_items.name: RegistrantPrivacy
nested_items.description: Specifies whether contact information is concealed from WHOIS queries. If the value is true, WHOIS ('who is') queries return contact information either for Amazon Registrar or for our registrar associate, Gandi. If the value is false, WHOIS queries return the information that you entered for the registrant contact (domain owner).

nested_items.name: TechPrivacy
nested_items.description: Specifies whether contact information is concealed from WHOIS queries. If the value is true, WHOIS ('who is') queries return contact information either for Amazon Registrar or for our registrar associate, Gandi. If the value is false, WHOIS queries return the information that you entered for the technical contact.

nested_items.name: RegistrarName
nested_items.description: Name of the registrar of the domain as identified in the registry.

nested_items.name: WhoIsServer
nested_items.description: The fully qualified name of the WHOIS server that can answer the WHOIS query for the domain.

nested_items.name: RegistrarUrl
nested_items.description: Web address of the registrar.

nested_items.name: AbuseContactEmail
nested_items.description: Email address to contact to report incorrect contact information for a domain, to report that the domain is being used to send spam, to report that someone is cybersquatting on a domain name, or report some other type of abuse.

nested_items.name: AbuseContactPhone
nested_items.description: Phone number for reporting abuse.

nested_items.name: RegistryDomainId
nested_items.description: Reserved for future use.

nested_items.name: CreationDate
nested_items.description: The date when the domain was created as found in the response to a WHOIS query. The date and time is in Unix time format and Coordinated Universal time (UTC).

nested_items.name: UpdatedDate
nested_items.description: The last updated date of the domain as found in the response to a WHOIS query. The date and time is in Unix time format and Coordinated Universal time (UTC).

nested_items.name: ExpirationDate
nested_items.description: The date when the registration for the domain is set to expire. The date and time is in Unix time format and Coordinated Universal time (UTC).

nested_items.name: Reseller
nested_items.description: Reseller of the domain. Domains registered or transferred using Route 53 domains will have "Amazon" as the reseller.

nested_items.name: DnsSec
nested_items.description: Deprecated.

nested_items.name: StatusList
nested_items.description: An array of domain name status codes, also known as Extensible Provisioning Protocol (EPP) status codes.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: DnssecKeys
nested_items.description: A complex type that contains information about the DNSSEC configuration.

nested_items.name: Algorithm
nested_items.description: The number of the public key's cryptographic algorithm according to an IANA assignment.

nested_items.name: Flags
nested_items.description: Defines the type of key. It can be either a KSK (key-signing-key, value 257) or ZSK (zone-signing-key, value 256). Using KSK is always encouraged. Only use ZSK if your DNS provider isn't Route 53 and you don't have KSK available.

nested_items.name: PublicKey
nested_items.description: The base64-encoded public key part of the key pair that is passed to the registry .

nested_items.name: DigestType
nested_items.description: The number of the DS digest algorithm according to an IANA assignment.

nested_items.name: Digest
nested_items.description: The delegation signer digest.

nested_items.name: KeyTag
nested_items.description: A numeric identification of the DNSKEY record referred to by this DS record.

nested_items.name: Id
nested_items.description: An ID assigned to each DS record created by AssociateDelegationSignerToDomain.
